To create a Gnome Launcher in Fedora 21 for Android Studio,
open a Terminal window and type:
  - sudo vi /usr/share/applications/asb.desktop
  
Edit the file like this:

[Desktop Entry]
Encoding=UTF-8
Name=Android Studio
Comment=Android Studio 1-0
Exec=asb
Icon=/opt/android-studio/bin/idea.png
Terminal=false
Type=Application
Categories=GNOME;Application;Development;
StartupNotify=true

Alternatively use the function provided by Android Studio:
  Menu --> Tools --> Create Desktop Entry...
